tml] and the Mo Bro\'s are making some serious progress. Although [Sloat|http://twitter.com/jsloat] has resorted to taking headshots in black and white to increase contrast...and Revo is starting to look more and more like Ron Jeremy everyday.\n\nh3. The Donation Situation\n\n{panel:borderWidth=3}_\"Movember is helping to support three vaccine research programs and move 12 new medicines from the laboratory to clinical trials. These may alleviate pain and suffering for the nearly 2.5 million men and their families who are currently facing prostate cancer in the U.S. How else can we say thank you from the bottom of their hearts and ours?\" said Dr. Jonathan Simons, Prostate Cancer Foundation President and CEO, \"Without Movember, the progress of those projects would have been hindered.\"\nKudos to the Sydney boys who picked up their game and have now overtaken the San Franciscans in their fundraising efforts._{panel}\n\nh3. Mo of the Week\n\nThe results are in and thanks to the [Survey Plugin|https://plugins.atlassian.com/plugin/details/195] it\'s clear to see that Todd was the clear favourite for the *Mo of the Week*.\n\n!MoOfTheWeek.png!\n\nh3. What about the other Mo Bro\'s?\n\n{widget:url=http://www.flickr.com/photos/mattnhodges/sets/72157622825313712/}',32839),(163878,'[!_Images^btn_previous.png!|Examples] [!_Images^btn_next.png|align=right!|Atlassian Colours]\\\\\n\\\\\n{tip:icon=false}Click on the *{_}Next{_}* and *{_}Previous{_}* buttons on the right and left of each page to navigate throughout this example.{tip}\n{section}\n{column}\n!Design_Home.png|width=603,height=403!\n{column}\n{column:width=1%}\n{column}\n{column}\n\nh1. Welcome\n\nThe Design Team space is a repository for visual aspects of the Atlassian brand. Catalogued within this space are all the tools and guidelines required to create new graphic designs for Atlassian.\n\n{pagetree:root=Example Design Team Page}\n{column}\n{section}\n[!_Images^btn_previous.png!|Examples] [!_Images^btn_next.png|ali